article.description: — Eric Mulder scored 19 points and grabbed 10 rebounds as Purdue Fort Wayne beat Detroit Mercy 91-56 on Sunday.

article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. -- — Eric Mulder scored 19 points and grabbed 10 rebounds as Purdue Fort Wayne beat Detroit Mercy 91-56 on Sunday. Jalen Jackson scored 15 points and added seven rebounds and five assists for the Mastadons (13-2, 4-0 Horizon League). Corey Hadnot II also had 15 points. The Titans (0-15, 0-4) were led in scoring by Edoardo Del Cadia, who finished with 16 points, 14 rebounds and two steals. Detroit Mercy also got 12 points from Marcus Tankersley. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
